Target: The OntoChangelog ontology provides a clear history of every change, acting as a digital paper trail that records who made a change, when it occurred, and a description of the action.

Comment: A specific event or process where a change occurs.
Label: Activity

Comment: A relationship that defines the specific object, record, or piece of data that was changed during the activity.
Label: affected

Comment: A relationship that defines the individual or automated system responsible for triggering the activity.
Label: was performed by

Comment: A property to store the precise date and time when the activity was completed.
Label: timestamp
